text: Ô-de-Selle is a commune. It is in Hauts-de-France in the Somme department in north France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Lœuilly (the seat), Neuville-lès-Lœuilly and Tilloy- lès-Conty.Arrêté préfectoral 7 December 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Somme
title: Ô-de-Selle
